---
import Base from '@layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base title="Privacy Policy" description="Varax Labs privacy policy. How we handle your data.">
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 py-16 sm:py-24">
    <h1 class="text-3xl font-semibold text-light-text dark:text-dark-text mb-2">Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p class="text-sm text-light-text-secondary dark:text-dark-text-secondary mb-10">Last updated: March 2026</p>

    <div class="prose">
      <h2>Overview</h2>
      <p>
        Varax Labs ("we", "us", "our") respects your privacy. This policy explains what data we collect,
        how we use it, and your rights regarding that data.
      </p>

      <h2>What We Collect</h2>
      <h3>Website Analytics</h3>
      <p>
        We use privacy-respecting analytics that do not use cookies and do not collect personally
        identifiable information. We track aggregate page views and referral sources to improve our
        content and user experience.
      </p>

      <h3>Email Subscriptions</h3>
      <p>
        If you subscribe to our newsletter, we collect your email address. We use this solely to send
        you product updates, technical content, and occasional announcements. You can unsubscribe at
        any time using the link in every email.
      </p>

      <h3>Purchases</h3>
      <p>
        Payment processing is handled entirely by Stripe. We do not store your credit card information.
        Stripe's privacy policy governs how your payment data is handled. We receive your email address
        and transaction details to fulfill your license.
      </p>

      <h2>Software Products</h2>
      <p>
        Varax Monitor and the Varax compliance platform run entirely within your Kubernetes cluster.
        No data is sent to our servers. Your cluster data, compliance results, and reports stay on
        your infrastructure.
      </p>

      <h2>Cookies</h2>
      <p>
        Our website does not use tracking cookies. We store a theme preference (dark/light mode) in
        your browser's localStorage, which is not transmitted to our servers.
      </p>

      <h2>Third Parties</h2>
      <p>
        We do not sell, trade, or share your personal information with third parties. Our service
        providers (analytics, email, payment processing) process data only as needed to provide their
        services.
      </p>

      <h2>Your Rights</h2>
      <p>
        You have the right to access, correct, or delete your personal data. To make a request,
        contact us at <a href="mailto:hello@varax.io">hello@varax.io</a>.
      </p>

      <h2>Changes</h2>
      <p>
        We may update this policy from time to time. Significant changes will be announced on our blog
        or via email to subscribers.
      </p>

      <h2>Contact</h2>
      <p>
        Questions about this policy? Email us at <a href="mailto:hello@varax.io">hello@varax.io</a>.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</Base>
